        "text": "Having cut in two the thread spun by a spider, the prince puts it together again, saying: 1 x 1. This is also the formula that we suggested above, because he who deciphers it holds the key to the secret that preserves him both from pseudomystical monism (whose formula is 1 = 1) and from abstract monotheism which is content to superimpose an Ens supremum on the multitude of beings (n + 1).",
