        "text": "We grew up in atwo-story house: matter downstairs, spirit upstairs. Corbin opens adoor in the stairwell and shows us awhole floor we never knew existed. The imaginal is not the imaginary — the imaginary is what you make up, the imaginal is what you discover. It has its own furniture, its own weather, its own laws. It is where prophets go when they see what others cannot. To refuse this third floor is to refuse Ibn 'Arabī before he has spoken aword."
