        "text": "Corbin is not writing atextbook. He is calling areader into being — the one who has felt the unease of belonging to atradition without being contained by it. If your spirituality requires abuilding, aceremony, acertificate of membership, this book will feel like athreat. If your spirituality has already outgrown its container, it will feel like ahomecoming."
