    "body": [
      {
        "kind": "ai",
        "text": "Swedenborg gives one of the clearest pre-Corbin descriptions of visionary geography. Heaven has societies, directions, houses, garments, speech, and distances. These correspond to inner states. Space in heaven is measured by love, wisdom, and affinity — miles."
      },
      {
        "kind": "source",
        "text": "XVII Changes of State of the Angels in Heaven. XXII Space in Heaven."
      },
      {
        "kind": "ai",
        "text": "The sequence matters. Swedenborg places space after state and time. Spiritual geography cannot be understood by location first. Understand the life of angels — love, wisdom, interior form — then space appears as the outer form of state. Asociety of love appears as adwelling. Wisdom appears as light. Difference appears as distance."
      },
      {
        "kind": "art",
        "art_id": "art_conjunction",
        "caption": "The heavenly city — a city of states, not of measurable distances."
      },
      {
        "kind": "source",
        "text": "By changes of state of angels, these alternations following one after another with variety."
      },
      {
        "kind": "ai",
        "text": "Two souls side by side in physical space may be worlds apart in spiritual space. Two souls separated by oceans may be neighbours. The inner becomes spatial: this is Swedenborg'sprecise imaginal rule. Place is primary — state is primary. Space appears as the visible shape of what the soul has become."
      },
      {
        "kind": "art",
        "art_id": "art_fludd_macrocosm",
        "caption": "Affinity as geography — distance measured by love, not miles."
      },
      {
        "kind": "source",
        "text": "In the spiritual world, all changes of place are changes of state of the interiors."
      },
      {
        "kind": "ai",
        "text": "This is why Corbin recognised Swedenborg as a Western witness — the same law governs Na-koja-Abad and Swedenborg'sheaven. Geography is the soul'sinterior made visible. The imaginal world has stable structures: the same inner states produce the same landscapes across traditions. Affinity replaces distance. State replaces location."
      },
      {
        "kind": "ai",
        "text": "Heaven is everywhere and nowhere. It is not aplace you go. It is what you become capable of perceiving when the inner state is ripe for it."
      }
    ],
