        "kind": "ai",
        "text": "Ficino'stheory of inspiration rests on adangerous distinction. One kind of madness breaks the soul downward. Another kind opens the ordinary ego so agodlike power can enter. Plato calls this divine mania. The inspired soul is seized by something beyond its usual range. The daimonic arrives as winged disturbance."
