        "text": "The essay is not about \"planetary music\" as avague concept. It is about embodied imitation — the human being becoming aperformative correspondence of the heavens. De vita III.21 opens with Ficino'sadvice to observe celestial positions and imitate them through speech, song, movement, dance, moral behaviour, and action. The sequence is not arbitrary. It descends from the most inward to the most outward: the music of the soul becomes the music of the body."
