        "kind": "source",
        "text": "\"Nine guides protect the scholar. Three heavenly: Mercury, Phoebus, and Venus. Three internal: will, intelligence, and memory. Three earthly: father, teacher, and physician. The father and teacher have been treated by classical authors — Plato, Aristotle, Plutarch, and Quintilian have already handled their formation. But the physician for scholars is still missing. Only aphysician can help scholars with salutary counsels and medicines.\""
