        "text": "The most obvious falsehood is technical: relying on apparatus, characters, surfaces, or procedures as if they themselves produce foreknowledge. But the more subtle falsehood is interpretive. Aperson may have adream and assume it is divine. Abody may tremble and assume it is possessed. Avoice may be heard and assumed to be agod. Asign may occur and be taken as prophecy. But the event itself is not enough. The source must be discerned."
