        "text": "One of the many issues that Farghānī addresses\nthroughout the book is wujūd.8\n1 Ontology If “ontology” is the study of existence, and if wujūd is the standard term for existence in Islamic thought, one can conclude that ontology lies at the heart not\nonly of Islamic philosophy but also of Sufism as it developed at the hands of Ibn\nʿArabī and those who followed in his footsteps."
